HEADWORD: Transumpt
<hw>Tran*sumpt"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>transumere</ets>, <ets>transumptum</ets>, to take from one to
another, in LL., to transcribe. See <er>Transume</er>.]</ety> <def>A
copy or exemplification of a record; a transcript.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Lord Herbert.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transumption</ent>⟦br⟧
